replies.body:
@Meddler , I don't think that is a great idea for Edge of Night.  Here is why:

As a mage, you are usually the target for the enemy team so they will be trying to catch you off guard and pick you off.  This is where the banshee's veil comes in.  It's shield (assuming not on cooldown) is always up, ready to save you from any unexpected attempt by the enemy team to catch you out. 
As a champion that builds edge of night, (usually assassins) you are going to be the one that is proactively making the plays and deciding when you want to strike.  In this scenario, it is a lot more helpful to be able to activate the spellshield before going in so you know it will be ready for you.

Did you know that some of your players play this champion released 5 years ago called Rek'Sai? {{champion:421}} 

This elusive champion used to be one of the top most fun junglers to play with her tunnels that give her mobility and high damage with her combos.

Now she's a old shell of her older dominant self, left to rot with mediocre damage, unfun mechanics only 2 skins, her newest one being a joke skin from Pool Party 2015. At this point, newer and more popular champions have gotten legendary and prestige skins (think {{champion:145}} {{champion:202}} {{champion:141}} {{champion:245}}  and most importantly {{champion:555}} ) or even reworks and changes that still keep them fresh to play to this patch.

Lots of us here Rek'Sai mains would love to see Rek'Sai updates, maybe give her a Quality skin to show how much Rioters care about us or, y'know, a better passive that does more for her, maybe let her bring her Void spawn with her to wreck some havoc, or a better more interesting and convoluted set of spells (making her Q and E more rewarding, impactful and interesting spells) like some of the better champions out there these days.

We Rek'Sai mains really appreciate your work and hope to see some Rek'Sai action this year at Worlds. {{champion:421}} {{item:3031}}
